messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.

Sure—when you say “later,” what timeframe do you have in mind? For example, later today, later this week, or after a specific date and time? Once I know that, I can pull up the right reminders for you.

Sure—“later today” means from now until the end of your day. Could you tell me your current local time (and, if it helps, your time zone)? Then I can pull up any todos scheduled from now until midnight.
I’m not sure about the exact time, but just check today’s schedule for me, please.

To pull up “later today” items I’ll need to know what “today” is in your locale. Could you let me know your current date (year, month, and day) and the time zone you’re in? Then I can find all your todos scheduled from now until midnight for today.
Running a bit blank on those details. Why not just check for any reminders today?

I can do that—just need a bit more info to define “today.” Could you let me know your current date (e.g. YYYY-MM-DD) or at least your time zone? With that I can pull up everything scheduled for today.
